name: GERBONG MAUT BONDOWOSO
description:
The carriage death incident, also known as the Bondowoso death train, is a historic incident that occurred on November 23, 1947 in Bondowoso, Indonesia during the Dutch occupation. In the midst of a guerrilla war between the people of Bondowoso and the Dutch colonialists, 100 people were arrested on suspicion of being revolutionaries.
